The Pinewood Box Caucus
-----------------------

Until somewhat recently, there was a code of omert=C3=A0 on Capitol Hill
regarding the most geriatric lawmakers, who comprise a substantial portion =
of senior leadership. While younger members enter the House by bounding up =
the marble steps on the chamber=E2=80=99s east front, an elevator on the ot=
her side of the room empties out waves of members in their 70s and 80s as t=
hey make their way to the floor. It=E2=80=99s not unusual to see an older m=
ember wave to reporters, colleagues, and staff while cruising by on a mobil=
ity scooter or staffer-escorted wheelchair. Earlier this month, a
photographer snapped a picture of a newly wheelchair-bound Rep. David Scott=
, the 79-year-old Democrat who recently lost his ranking position on the Ag=
riculture Committee. =E2=80=9CWho gave you the right to take my picture, as=
shole?=E2=80=9D Scott
shouted ( https://x.com/MZanona/status/1869475925005566254?ref_src=3Dtwsrc%=
5Etfw%7Ctwcamp%5Etweetembed%7Ctwterm%5E1869475925005566254%7Ctwgr%5E39c957a=
69661837c169a743156106ce6c38c4107%7Ctwcon%5Es1_&ref_url=3Dhttps%3A%2F%2Fwww=
=2Elatintimes.com%2Fdemocratic-lawmaker=
-snaps-journalist-taking-his-photo-pub=
lic-who-gave-you-right-hole-569798&utm_campaign=3DThe+Best+%26+The+Brightes=
t+-+SUBSCRIBERS+%2812%2F30%2F24%29&utm_content=3DThe+Best+%26+The+Brightest=
+-+SUBSCRIBERS+%2812%2F29%2F24%29&utm_medium=3Demail_action&utm_source=3Dcu=
stomer.io&utm_term=3Df6c60617da42abd12a ) at him. (That would be the First =
Amendment=E2=80=A6)=C2=A0

=C2=A0

There=E2=80=99s an off-color term for these senescent legislators: the Pine=
wood Box Caucus, the implication being that the only way they=E2=80=99ll le=
ave the Capitol is in a coffin. Alas, in Congress, seniority is often a fun=
ction of, well=E2=80=A6 seniority. Members in their eighth or ninth decade =
of life may risk overstaying their welcome, but it=E2=80=99s only after man=
y terms of service that they finally gain real clout=E2=80=94ascending to w=
ildly powerful committee positions where they
can best help constituents and pass legacy bills. In Granger=E2=80=99s case=
, she reached the peak of her power as the first Republican woman to serve =
as Appropriations chair=E2=80=94possibly the most coveted job in the entire=
 House=E2=80=94only in her last term. Had she retired earlier, she would ha=
ve given up her shot at the gavel after a quarter-century of patiently wait=
ing her turn.

=C2=A0

The gerontocracy was somewhat weakened this past month when
certain Democrats, emboldened by forcing Joe Biden off the presidential tic=
ket, and still frustrated by failed efforts to force Dianne Feinstein and R=
uth Bader Ginsburg to retire, launched a multifront campaign to replace sev=
eral ( https://puck.news/the-democrats-changing-on-the-guard-one-committee-=
at-a-time/?utm_campaign=3DThe+Best+%26+The+Brightest+-+SUBSCRIBERS+%2812%2F=
30%2F24%29&utm_content=3DThe+Best+%26+The+Brightest+-+SUBSCRIBERS+%2812%2F2=
9%2F24%29&utm_medium=3Demail_action&utm_source=3Dcustomer.io&utm_term=3Df6c=
60617da42abd12a ) committee ranking chairs with much younger colleagues. Af=
ter an
election in which the oldest-ever president will be replaced by the second-=
oldest president-elect, there=E2=80=99s more desire than ever for leadershi=
p to resemble the future of the country, rather than its past.

